45
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:28,390
I will always remember

46
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:30,110
that there's someone

47
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:32,290
waiting for me to come back safely

48
00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:34,310
and waiting for me to come home.

49
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:41,700
Nan Chu.

50
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:43,550
From now on,

51
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:46,450
my life belongs to the country.

52
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:49,010
But my heart

53
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,270
belongs to you.

54
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,390
Let's be together.

55
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:23,410
Liu.

56
00:03:23,410 --> 00:03:23,870
Wait.

57
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:24,290
Lin.

58
00:03:24,290 --> 00:03:25,720
Come and persuade Yang.

59
00:03:26,350 --> 00:03:26,850
What's wrong?

60
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:30,040
He fired the nanny that the station hired for him.

61
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,430
It's useless no matter how Yu and I try to persuade him.

62
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:32,180
Come here now.

63
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:33,020
Hurry up.

64
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,450
You scared me.

65
00:03:34,450 --> 00:03:35,630
You made it sound so serious.

66
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:36,470
I thought something happened.

67
00:03:36,470 --> 00:03:37,600
I'll take a leave and come over.

68
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,030
Okay.

69
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,030
I'm fine.

70
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:46,170
I'm doing just fine.

71
00:03:46,170 --> 00:03:47,010
I'm really fine.

72
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,060
If you have the time,

73
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:50,160
it'd be great for you to go back to the station and do some work.

74
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:51,710
Why are all of you

75
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,940
coming to me every day?

76
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:55,280
Is there really nothing to do at the station?

77
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,270
Who is this again?

78
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,740
Who did you call over this time?

79
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,210
Savior, you're finally here.

80
00:04:02,210 --> 00:04:02,930
You have no idea

81
00:04:02,930 --> 00:04:04,140
how stubborn he is.

82
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:05,110
Yu and I have been persuading him for a long time.

83
00:04:05,110 --> 00:04:06,080
You should talk to him now.

84
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:07,710
Luxiao.

85
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:11,330
What are you doing here?

86
00:04:12,670 --> 00:04:13,640
What do you mean?

87
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,640
I'm here to see you.

88
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:16,790
What's wrong with the nanny we got you?

89
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:17,880
Why did you fire her?

90
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,310
I don't need a nanny.

91
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,190
I really don't.

92
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:21,490
I'm fine on my own.

93
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:23,460
Why did you get me a nanny?

94
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:25,270
It's a waste of money.

95
00:04:26,530 --> 00:04:27,660
It's not a waste.

96
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:28,460
If there's a nanny here,

97
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:29,470
she can help you clean up

98
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,520
and cook for you. Isn't that convenient?

99
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,110
Convenient?

100
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:31,950
How is it convenient?

101
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:34,430
It's more inconvenient for me

102
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:35,640
with an outsider in my home.

103
00:04:36,230 --> 00:04:37,280
My leg is broken,

104
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,630
but my arms are fine.

105
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,310
Do you really think I'm useless?

106
00:04:40,310 --> 00:04:41,100
No, no, no.

107
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:43,330
What are you thinking?

108
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:45,980
We're all just sincerely trying to help.

109
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:50,550
I know.

110
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:52,320
I know you don't mean that.

111
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,420
But I can do everything by myself.

112
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:55,760
Can you trust me?

113
00:04:56,770 --> 00:04:57,650
I still have my arms

114
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,170
and the wheelchair you gave me.

115
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,730
I can take care of the basics in living

116
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:04,410
by myself.

117
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:06,300
Really.

118
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,840
Go back now.

119
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,560
I beg you.

120
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,450
Can you stop hanging out here?

121
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,340
Don't make me think

122
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:23,100
that I'm dragging you down.

123
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:26,210
Yang.

124
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,430
How...

125
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:28,480
How could you say that?

126
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:28,860
Enough.

127
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:29,440
Enough, Yu.

128
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:29,950
All right.

129
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,420
Forget it.

130
00:05:32,170 --> 00:05:33,520
Yang is comfortable at home.

131
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,650
He should do what makes him comfortable.

132
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:36,330
Let's go.

133
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:37,090
We're leaving.

134
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:37,840
Yang.

135
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,890
Think about it again.

136
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,670
If there's someone helping you out at home,

137
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:42,090
it'll be convenient for you too.

138
00:05:42,090 --> 00:05:43,090
Let's go.

139
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,980
Leave Yang alone.

140
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:45,870
All right.

141
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:48,090
You don't have a nanny at home from now on.

142
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:48,970
Cheer up.

143
00:05:49,230 --> 00:05:50,020
Don't lose your temper.

144
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:52,170
We have to go now.

145
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,430
Call me if there's anything.

146
00:05:58,550 --> 00:05:59,180
All right.

147
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,310
Let's go.

148
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,570
We're leaving, Yang.

149
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:02,880
Talk to him again.

150
00:06:03,090 --> 00:06:03,840
Talk to him.

151
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,980
Let's go.

152
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:05,730
It's okay. Let's go.

153
00:06:17,790 --> 00:06:18,580
Lin Luxiao.

154
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:20,980
Are you here to help us?

155
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,540
You know Instructor Yang's situation.

156
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,940
His parents passed away early.

157
00:06:25,090 --> 00:06:26,230
He's always been alone.

158
00:06:26,230 --> 00:06:27,450
All these years,

159
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:29,000
he has always regarded the fire station as his home.

160
00:06:29,210 --> 00:06:30,510
The situation is special.

161
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:31,770
Don't keep going against him.

162
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,750
Go along with his wishes and let him be happy.

163
00:06:34,210 --> 00:06:35,090
That won't do.

164
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:36,100
How can we leave him alone

165
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:36,600
at home?

166
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,660
Didn't you say he has phantom limb pains?

167
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,770
I heard that it's very painful when it happens.

168
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:43,150
There's nothing we can do.

169
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:45,170
I'll just come and visit him more often when I'm free.

170
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:47,060
When are you free?

171
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:48,860
The Fire Investigation Department is busy enough.

172
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,960
The problem now is that Yang doesn't talk much

173
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,060
and you don't talk much either.

174
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:53,530
How can you not chat with him?

175
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:55,330
How about this?

176
00:06:55,330 --> 00:06:55,960
When it's my turn,

177
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,310
I'll chat with him nonstop.

178
00:06:57,770 --> 00:06:59,200
If it isn't my turn,

179
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,830
I'll call him to harass him.

180
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,440
Count me in.

181
00:07:03,770 --> 00:07:04,870
Coincidentally, it's my turn to take a day off.

182
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,080
Forget it.

183
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:07,090
If you're on leave,

184
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:08,770
go home and accompany your family.

185
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:10,660
I videocall them every day. It's the same thing.

186
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:11,880
How is it the same thing?

187
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:13,900
Besides, there are many things to do at the station.

188
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,070
If you two are here,

189
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,160
who will take care of the station?

190
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:17,090
Are you quitting your jobs?

191
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,220
He's right.

192
00:07:18,770 --> 00:07:19,400
Yu, how about this?

193
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:20,990
The two of us can take turns.

194
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,550
Okay.

195
00:07:23,090 --> 00:07:23,640
All right.

196
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:24,520
I'll send you off.

197
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:24,980
Let's go.

198
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,410
I've made it for you.

199
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,300
I can move.

200
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,770
I don't need you to help me with every little thing.

201
00:10:02,940 --> 00:10:05,380
I'm now transferred to the brigade's Fire Investigation Department.

202
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:07,810
I can't use up my annual leave days either.

203
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,170
It's just right. I can accompany you here.

204
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,890
Don't feel pressured.

205
00:10:11,890 --> 00:10:13,610
It's like a vacation for me being here.

206
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:17,390
Hello.

207
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:18,520
Hello, you have a package.

208
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,660
Please put it at the door.

209
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:20,920
Your community doesn't allow us to enter.

210
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,010
Just let the guards know.

211
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:23,560
You can't bring it up?

212
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,360
No.

213
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:25,120
Fine.

214
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,000
I'll go down and get it.

215
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:26,670
I'm sorry about that.

216
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:27,760
Okay.

217
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:30,410
What did you buy this time?

218
00:10:30,910 --> 00:10:31,710
You're wasting money.

219
00:10:31,710 --> 00:10:32,890
I have everything I need at home.

220
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:34,400
I bought some daily necessities.

221
00:10:34,650 --> 00:10:35,740
It's too late to buy them

222
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:36,750
only when you run out of them.

223
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,640
It's weird that your community doesn't allow

224
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,650
mail carriers in.

225
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:40,410
There's no choice.

226
00:10:40,410 --> 00:10:41,250
There have been many theft cases.

227
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,010
Do you need me to get you anything?

228
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,520
No need.

229
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:45,990
Okay, wait for me.

230
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,070
I'm fine.

231
00:10:51,070 --> 00:10:51,620
Go ahead.

232
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,050
Okay.

233
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:53,760
I'll be right up.

234
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:54,770
Okay, go ahead.

235
00:11:58,310 --> 00:11:59,150
Yang.

236
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,460
Where is

237
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:03,400
your electricity card?

238
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:04,870
It's out of credit.

239
00:12:07,550 --> 00:12:08,180
Yang.

240
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,400
Don't come over.

241
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:11,540
What's wrong?

242
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:12,890
Yang!

243
00:12:13,310 --> 00:12:14,150
Don't come over.

244
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:15,160
How did you fall?

245
00:12:15,410 --> 00:12:16,290
Come on. Get up.

246
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:17,510
Get up.

247
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,770
-Come on. Get up.
-Don't come over.

248
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:20,870
Don't come over.

249
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:23,140
Yang.

250
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,070
Don't move. It's okay.

251
00:12:25,070 --> 00:12:27,500
Don't touch me!

252
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:30,190
Don't touch me!

253
00:12:30,190 --> 00:12:31,160
Yang.

254
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,640
Don't touch me.

255
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,050
All right.

256
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:13,660
Leave.

257
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,620
Please.

258
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:22,610
Can you leave me with some dignity?

259
00:13:24,660 --> 00:13:26,550
I'm useless now.

260
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:27,060
How...

261
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:30,290
How long can you take care of me?

262
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:38,650
Just go.

263
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:45,660
Yang.

264
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:48,770
It's been so many years.

265
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:52,170
We've always been by each other's sides.

266
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,530
Since I joined the fire station,

267
00:13:58,310 --> 00:13:59,650
you entered earlier than me

268
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:02,510
and are a few years older than me.

269
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:05,870
So you always treated me as your younger brother.

270
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:08,180
Later,

271
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:10,280
I became the director

272
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:12,170
and you became an instructor,

273
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,390
and you've always been helping me by my side.

274
00:14:18,170 --> 00:14:19,140
All these years,

275
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,360
no matter what danger

276
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:23,760
or what situation we encounter,

277
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:26,280
you always charged in front of me

278
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:29,010
and protected me.

279
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:32,370
Didn't you say

280
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:34,300
that a good relationship between a director

281
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:36,520
and an instructor

282
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,890
should be like that of a married couple?

283
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,540
A married couple,

284
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:45,340
right?

285
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,380
This time, you also protected everyone

286
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,900
